menuconfig PKG_CANOPENNODE_USING_GATEWAY_ASCII
    bool "CiA 309-3 ASCII gateway"
    default n
    select PKG_CANOPENNODE_USING_FIFO
    select PKG_CANOPENNODE_FIFO_ASCII_COMMANDS
    help
        Enable CO_gateway_ascii.c and CO_CONFIG_GTW_ASCII. This option only
        compiles CANopenNode ASCII gateway support and related helpers. The
        default RT-Thread application wrapper does not create a serial/TCP
        command transport and does not schedule gateway processing from its
        internal mainline thread.

        Applications that use the ASCII gateway must provide the command
        transport, initialize the gateway objects, and call the CANopenNode
        gateway processing path from an application-owned thread or event loop.

        Gateway command groups depend on SDO client, NMT master and/or LSS master
        options below.

